article.headline: Illinois State 77, Evansville 58
article.story: NORMAL, Ill. (AP) -- Trey Guidry had 25 points in only 31 minutes as Illinois State beat Evansville 77-58 Tuesday night. Guidry had five assists and four rebounds to go along with his scoring. Teammates Lorenzo Gordon and Gregg Alexander had 11 points each. Alexander led the Redbirds (14-5, 6-3 Missouri Valley) with seven rebounds. Lucious Wagner, Evansville's leading scorer, could only muster up 14 total points. Teammate Bradley Strickland had 12 points, but no other Evansville player had more than seven points. Illinois State held a tenuous 27-26 lead at the end of the first half, but exploded for 50 points in the second half, compared to 32 for the Purple Aces (10-6, 4-6 MVC). Guidry led the charge, scoring 17 of his 25 points in the second half.
